{"questionId":"11773","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the regression line of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ln}}\\left( {T - 25} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>25</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> on&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ln}}\\left( {T - 25} \\right) =&nbsp; - 0.00870t + 3.89\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>25</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0.00870</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3.89</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11773","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.15b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the regression line of ln ( T − 25 ) on t .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}